## 6. Key Class Responsibilities

### `ThisAddIn.cs`

The VSTO entry point. VS generates this. Extend with:

- `ThisAddIn_Startup`: initialize the DI container (`Bootstrapper`), hook into `Application.Inspectors.NewInspector`
- `ThisAddIn_Shutdown`: dispose the DI container, release COM objects
- Hold a reference to the collection of active `InspectorWrapper` instances

```csharp
// Rough structure only — implement to match your needs
private void ThisAddIn_Startup(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    Bootstrapper.Initialize();
    Application.Inspectors.NewInspector += Inspectors_NewInspector;
}

private void Inspectors_NewInspector(Outlook.Inspector inspector)
{
    var item = inspector.CurrentItem;
    if (item is Outlook.AppointmentItem)
        _inspectorWrappers.Add(new InspectorWrapper(inspector));
}
```

### `InspectorWrapper.cs`

Wraps an Outlook Inspector (appointment/meeting window). Responsibilities:

- Attach to inspector's `Close` event to clean up
- Register a custom task pane (`SalesforceTaskPaneControl`) via `CustomTaskPanes.Add()`
- Attach `AppointmentEventHandler` to the inspector's appointment item events

### `Infrastructure/Bootstrapper.cs`

Initializes the Castle Windsor IoC container. Registers all services:

- `OutlookMeetingService`
- `RegistryConfiguration`
- HTTP clients (stub for now)
- NLog logger

```csharp
public static class Bootstrapper
{
    public static IWindsorContainer Container { get; private set; }

    public static void Initialize()
    {
        Container = new WindsorContainer();
        Container.AddFacility<LoggingFacility>(f => f.UseNLog());
        Container.Register(
            Component.For<IOutlookMeetingService>().ImplementedBy<OutlookMeetingService>(),
            Component.For<IRegistryConfiguration>().ImplementedBy<RegistryConfiguration>()
            // register remaining services here
        );
        ServiceLocator.SetLocatorProvider(() => new WindsorServiceLocator(Container));
    }
}
```

### `Infrastructure/WindsorServiceLocator.cs`

Adapter between Castle Windsor and `CommonServiceLocator.ServiceLocator`.
Implement `IServiceLocator` backed by `IWindsorContainer`.

### `Infrastructure/RegistryConfiguration.cs`

Reads add-in configuration from Windows Registry.
Key: `HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Nomura\IBD\SalesforceOutlook`
Settings to read: API endpoint URL, feature flags, environment name.

### `OutlookEventHandlers/AppointmentEventHandler.cs`

Hooks Outlook appointment item events:
- `Write` — triggered when an appointment is saved
- `Send` — triggered when a meeting request is sent
- `BeforeDelete` — triggered before deletion

Delegates to `SaveAndSendEventHandler` and `DeleteEventHandler`.

### `OutlookEventHandlers/ThrottledEventHandler.cs`

Wraps an event handler to debounce rapid successive triggers.
Use a `System.Threading.Timer` reset on each call; only fire after a quiet period.

### `OutlookEventHandlers/EventTracker.cs`

Tracks in-flight event processing to prevent duplicate handling of the same appointment.
Use a `HashSet<string>` of entry IDs with locking.

### `OutlookService/OutlookMeetingService.cs`

Core service. Builds a `MeetingRequest` DTO from an `Outlook.AppointmentItem` and dispatches it.
For now, stub the dispatch (where Salesforce HTTP call would go).

### `OutlookService/MeetingRequestDtoBuilder.cs`

Translates `Outlook.AppointmentItem` properties into a `MeetingRequest` DTO:
- Subject, body, start/end times
- Organizer, required/optional attendees (from `Recipients`)
- Location, GlobalAppointmentID

### `OutlookService/AddressParserService.cs`

Resolves SMTP addresses from Outlook recipient objects.
Handles Exchange and SMTP address types.

### `OutlookService/EntryIdService.cs` + `HexReader.cs`

Utilities for decoding Outlook Entry IDs (used as stable identifiers for appointments).

### `View/SalesforceTaskPaneControl.cs`

A `UserControl` added as a VSTO custom task pane in appointment windows.
Hosts the `HiddenPanelUserControl` (WebView) and any toolbar/status UI.

### `View/HiddenPanelUserControl.cs`

A `UserControl` that embeds a `Microsoft.Toolkit.Forms.UI.Controls.WebView`.
Used to render a web-based Salesforce UI panel (stub for now — just initialize the control).

### `View/SfApptItemRibbon.cs` / `SfExplorerRibbon.cs`

Ribbon XML add-ins. Add via: **Project → Add New Item → Ribbon (XML)**.
- `SfApptItemRibbon`: adds buttons to the appointment inspector ribbon
- `SfExplorerRibbon`: adds buttons to the main Outlook explorer ribbon

