## 7. Configuration Files to Create

### `NLog.config`

Add to the main VSTO project, set **Copy to Output Directory: Copy always**.

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<nlog xmlns="http://www.nlog-project.org/schemas/NLog.xsd"
      xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <targets>
    <target name="file"
            xsi:type="File"
            fileName="${tempdir}/Nomura.IBD.Salesforce.Outlook/Log.txt"
            layout="[UTC]|${level:uppercase=true}|${logger}|${threadid}|${message}|${exception:format=tostring}"
            archiveEvery="Day"
            archiveNumbering="DateAndSequence"
            maxArchiveFiles="5"
            archiveAboveSize="10485760" />
  </targets>
  <rules>
    <logger name="*" minlevel="Debug" writeTo="file" />
  </rules>
</nlog>
```

### `packages.config`

Managed automatically by VS when installing NuGet packages in `packages.config` mode.
Verify the file exists at the project root and is not replaced by a `<PackageReference>` in the `.csproj`.

